title: Why the 1% Women Aren't on Apps #DatingTips #MeetTheOnePercent #BeyondDatingApps #TrueConnections

channel_info.title: Robbie Kramer
channel_info.description:
I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.

transcription: {"text": "How are you meeting guys now? Wait, before you, I can never go on a dating website. I wanted to look smart and say, I bet you don't use all my data. Oh, really? First off, I'm not against that. Yeah, I'm not. Cause I know a lot of people like are on Raya or like Hinge or whatever, Bumble, whatever, and not judging the people that are on it. I just personally don't use it. It sounds kind of qwerty, but I feel like I believe in faith. And if I'm meant to meet you, I will meet you. If it's in the grocery store, if it's, you know, at a party, or even if it's in my DMs, I don't care. I feel like I'm meant to meet that person for a reason. Like the universe is like bringing us together as corny as that sounds still. But I just don't believe in like looking at an app and be like, well, maybe I like him. Maybe I don't like him. Well, that activity is so toxic, right? You're sitting there, you're swiping. And maybe if you're running on the treadmill, doing something, then you can justify it a little bit. Like you're forcing yourself to be into a guy that you may not even be into. And then he may not even look like his actual images. And then you meet them in person. And you're like, wow, you look.
